    narr:narration """This hub aggregates novelty assessments across diverse artifacts, consistently identifying a high-originality baseline that eschews standard startup tropes. The thematic span centers on [fresh metaphors and conceptual framing](narr:RubricAssess_Novelty), such as [continuation-machines](narr:Rubric_Novelty_ScarletDame) and [code-as-compilation-output](narr:Rubric_Assess_Novelty). Assessments frequently highlight a [worldview-vs-skills distinction](narr:Rubric_Novelty_YC_Call) and [distinctive taxonomies](narr:Assessment_Novelty_YC), often supported by lexical diversity metrics (type-token ratios ~0.67–0.68). The material spans [GTM and revenue models](narr:Assess_Novelty_RevenueModelTAM), [pilot planning](narr:Rubric_Novelty_PilotPlan), and [technical demo beats](narr:Rubric_Novelty_YCDemoBeats). While the overall trajectory favors high originality, the assessments consistently document a [tension between unique insights and necessary genre-based boilerplate](narr:RubricAssess_Novelty_GTM), particularly in structured documents like bios, discovery calls, and pilot retainers.""" ;
